View.CheckCode:
/* Sample Surveillance System Check Code This system and the Check Code contained here is for demonstration purposes only. All names and places used in these sample data tables are fictional. Any resemblence to actual persons or places is coincidental. */
/* -------- COMMENTS --------- Multi-line comments are created using a slash-asterisk to begin the comment and an asterisk-slash to end the comment. You can add comments to the Check Code to describe what is happening, or comment out lines to prevent them from running. Simply wrap lines you want to comment with the slash-asterisk and asterisk-slash symbols. */
// Single lines can be commented by adding a double slash in the beginning of the line.
/* XXXXXXXXXXX DEFINED VARIABLES XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX Defined variables are used to hold calculated or assigned values in memory for use in other sections of the Check Code. */
DefineVariables DEFINE EnteredDate DATEFORMAT DEFINE ReferenceDate DATEFORMAT DEFINE DateError YN DEFINE HighLightField YN DEFINE ZipError YN DEFINE ZipToTest TEXTINPUT DEFINE ZipAsNumeric NUMERIC End-DefineVariables
/* XXXXXXXXXXX SUB ROUTINES XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX Sub-routines are blocks of statements that can be called from several places in within the Check Code blocks. */
Sub DateERR_Future //This routine gives a simple dialog. //It is called when a date is greater than the date of the computer.
DIALOG "Date cannot be a future date." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date"
End-Sub
Sub DateERR_EarlierThanDOB DIALOG "Date cannot be earlier than Birth Date. Please check both dates." TITLETEXT="Date Discrepancy" End-Sub
Sub ValidateZip //This routine checks the format of the Zip Code field. //In the United States, some postal zone codes (zip codes) begin with zeros. //Therefore, a Number field cannot be used nation-wide since Number fields do not store leading zeros. //Also, Zip codes must have at least 5 digits and are in the range from 00501 to 96999. //These business rules are enforced here.
IF NOT ZipToTest = (.) THEN IF STRLEN( ZipToTest ) < 5 THEN ASSIGN ZipError = (+) DIALOG "Zip Code requires 5 numbers to be valid. Please enter 5 numbers only." TITLETEXT="Invalid Zip Code" ELSE ASSIGN ZipAsNumeric = TXTTONUM( ZipToTest ) //Zip containing letters or symbols will return null from the TXTTONUM function. IF NOT ZipAsNumeric = (.) THEN IF ZipAsNumeric < 501 OR ZipAsNumeric > 96999 THEN ASSIGN ZipError = (+) DIALOG "Valid U.S.P.S. zip codes are from 00501 to 96999." TITLETEXT="Zip Code out of range." ELSE ASSIGN ZipError = (-) END-IF ELSE ASSIGN ZipError = (+) DIALOG "Zip code may contain invalid characters (letters or symbols). Please enter only numbers for the zip code." TITLETEXT="Invalid characters" END-IF END-IF ELSE ASSIGN ZipError = (-) END-IF
End-Sub
/* XXXXXXXXXXX DATE VALIDATION XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX */
Sub GreaterThanReference //This routine simply compares the date being tested (EnteredDate) with a reference. //If the date being tested is greater than the reference date, // then the DateError flag is set to (+) which means Yes or True.
//First, the DateError flag is set to (-) whinh means No or False. ASSIGN DateError = (-)
//When this IF-THEN condition is True, it sets the DateError flag to True. If EnteredDate > ReferenceDate Then ASSIGN DateError = (+) End-If
End-Sub
Sub LessThanReference ASSIGN DateError = (-) IF EnteredDate < ReferenceDate Then ASSIGN DateError = (+) End-If End-Sub
Sub CheckBirthDate //Most dates in this example system should not be before the date of birth of the patient. //This routine tests the date entered to make sure it is not less than Birth Date.
If NOT Birthdate = (.) THEN ASSIGN ReferenceDate = BirthDate CALL LessThanReference If DateError Then CALL DateERR_EarlierThanDOB ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If
End-Sub
Sub CheckSystemDate //Most dates in this example cannot occur in the future. //Therefore, this routine tests the date entered against the date of the system. //The SYSTEMDATE is a standard function in Epi Info 7 that returns the date of the //computer's internal clock.
ASSIGN ReferenceDate = SYSTEMDATE CALL GreaterThanReference If DateError Then CALL DateERR_Future ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If
End-Sub
Sub CheckDates //This routine simply calls other routines. You can add routines similar to the ones above, //then call them here to have them check each date that needs to be validated.
Call CheckBirthDate Call CheckSystemDate
End-Sub
/* XXXXXXXXXXX PAGE 1: PERSON XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX Adding page separators like this is optional, but it helps to locate blocks of code. Epi Info(tm)7 adds new command blocks to the very bottom. If you have time, you may want to cut and paste new blocks into the appropriate page sections to keep the Check Code organized. */
/* Most command blocks can have a Before section, an After section, or both. Some command blocks, such as those for CommandButtons, have a Click section. Each section must have a starting and ending line. Commands within Before...End-Before are run before data entry occurs in that field, page, record, or form. Commands within the After...End-After statements are run after data entry when the cursor leaves. */
Page Person //Code in this page block will run each time a page is displayed in the Enter tool. Before IF Sex="Female" THEN ENABLE Pregnant ELSE DISABLE Pregnant END End-Before End-Page
Field EventDate After ASSIGN HighLightField = (-) ASSIGN EnteredDate = EventDate CALL CheckDates //The HighLightField flag is set to True within the CheckDates routine when // there is a discrepancy with one of the date validation checks. If HighLightField Then HIGHLIGHT EventDate Else UNHIGHLIGHT EventDate ASSIGN Year=YEAR(EventDate) ASSIGN Week=EpiWeek(EventDate) End-If End-After End-Field
Field LastName After IF Entered = (.) THEN ASSIGN Entered = SYSTEMDATE END End-After End-Field
Field FirstName After //The AUTOSEARCH command will identify if any of the search fields already exist //in the data tables. If no match is found, no dialog is displayed. //If a match is found, only the fields following the DISPLAYLIST keyword are shown in //the Autosearch dialog. Double-clicking a row in the dialog will discard any changes //made in the current record and jump to the record clicked.
AUTOSEARCH FirstName LastName DISPLAYLIST LastName FirstName BirthDate CaseID Age
End-After End-Field
Field BirthDate After IF NOT BirthDate = (.) THEN ASSIGN HighLightField = (-) ASSIGN EnteredDate = BirthDate Call CheckSystemDate IF HighLightField THEN HIGHLIGHT BirthDate ELSE IF NOT EventDate = (.) THEN IF BirthDate > EventDate THEN HIGHLIGHT BirthDate EventDate DIALOG "Birth Date cannot be later than Event Date. Please check both dates." TITLETEXT="Date Discrepancy" ELSE UNHIGHLIGHT BirthDate EventDate IF YEARS(BirthDate, EventDate) > 1 THEN ASSIGN Age = YEARS(BirthDate, EventDate) ASSIGN AgeType = "Years" ELSE IF MONTHS(BirthDate, EventDate) > 1 THEN ASSIGN Age = MONTHS(BirthDate, EventDate) ASSIGN AgeType = "Months" ELSE IF DAYS(BirthDate, EventDate) > 1 THEN ASSIGN Age = DAYS(BirthDate, EventDate) ASSIGN AgeType = "Days" ELSE DIALOG "Please verify Event Date and Birth Date." TITLETEXT="Error in dates." END-IF END-IF END-IF END-IF END-IF END-IF END-IF End-After End-Field
Field Sex After IF NOT Sex="Female" THEN ASSIGN Pregnant=(-) DISABLE Pregnant ELSE ENABLE Pregnant END End-After End-Field
Field ZipCode After ASSIGN ZipError = (-) ASSIGN ZipToTest = ZipCode CALL ValidateZip IF ZipError = (+) THEN HIGHLIGHT ZipCode ELSE UNHIGHLIGHT ZipCode END-IF End-After End-Field
Field cmdCaseDefinitions Click EXECUTE WAITFOREXIT "http://www.cdc.gov/" End-Click End-Field
Field SurveillanceDashboard Click EXECUTE WAITFOREXIT "AnalysisDashboard.exe .\Projects\Sample\SampleSurveillance.cvs7" End-Click End-Field
/* XXXXXXXXXXX PAGE 2: HOSPITAL INFO XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX */
Page [Hospital Info] Before IF LabConfirmed = (-) THEN DISABLE LabDate Specimen ELSE ENABLE LabDate Specimen END-IF IF Hospitalized = (-) THEN DISABLE DateAdmitted DateDischarged DoctorsName HospitalCity HospitalName ELSE ENABLE DateAdmitted DateDischarged DoctorsName HospitalCity HospitalName END-IF End-Before End-Page
Field Hospitalized After IF Hospitalized = (-) THEN DISABLE DateAdmitted DateDischarged DoctorsName HospitalCity HospitalName ELSE ENABLE DateAdmitted DateDischarged DoctorsName HospitalCity HospitalName END-IF End-After End-Field
Field DateAdmitted After ASSIGN HighLightField = (-) ASSIGN EnteredDate = DateAdmitted CALL CheckDates IF HighLightField = (-) THEN If NOT EventDate = (.) Then ASSIGN ReferenceDate = EventDate CALL LessThanReference If DateError Then DIALOG "Date Admitted cannot be earlier than Event Date." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date" ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If IF HighLightField = (-) THEN If NOT DateDischarged = (.) Then ASSIGN ReferenceDate = DateDischarged CALL GreaterThanReference If DateError Then DIALOG "Date Admitted cannot be later than Date Discharged." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date" ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If End-If End-If If HighLightField Then HIGHLIGHT DateAdmitted Else UNHIGHLIGHT DateAdmitted End-If End-After End-Field
Field DateDischarged After ASSIGN HighLightField = (-) ASSIGN EnteredDate = DateDischarged CALL CheckDates IF HighLightField = (-) THEN If NOT EventDate = (.) Then ASSIGN ReferenceDate = EventDate CALL LessThanReference If DateError Then DIALOG "Date Discharged cannot be earlier than Event Date." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date" ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If IF HighLightField = (-) THEN If NOT DateAdmitted = (.) Then ASSIGN ReferenceDate = DateAdmitted CALL LessThanReference If DateError Then DIALOG "Date Discharged cannot be earlier than Date Admitted." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date" ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If End-If End-If
If HighLightField Then HIGHLIGHT DateDischarged Else UNHIGHLIGHT DateDischarged End-If End-After End-Field
Field LabConfirmed After //add code here IF LabConfirmed = (-) THEN DISABLE LabDate Specimen CLEAR LabDate Specimen ELSE ENABLE LabDate Specimen END-IF End-After End-Field
/* XXXXXXXXXXX PAGE 3: CASE REPORT XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX */
Page [Case Report] Before //This section illustrates three ways to compare values. //If the condition is true, the corresponding Relate button becomes enabled. //This method allows for conditionally related records to be collected.
IF Disease LIKE "HEP*" THEN ENABLE Hepatitis ELSE DISABLE Hepatitis END-IF
IF Disease ="LYME" THEN ENABLE Lyme ELSE DISABLE Lyme END-IF IF EVENTCODE="10150" OR EVENTCODE="10590" OR EVENTCODE="10650" OR EVENTCODE="10640" THEN ENABLE Meningitis ELSE DISABLE Meningitis END-IF End-Before End-Page
Field ReportDate After ASSIGN HighLightField = (-) ASSIGN EnteredDate = ReportDate CALL CheckDates If NOT (EventDate = (.) OR HighLightField) Then ASSIGN ReferenceDate = EventDate CALL LessThanReference If DateError Then DIALOG "Report date cannot be earlier than Event Date." TITLETEXT="Invalid Date" ASSIGN HighLightField = (+) End-If End-If If HighLightField Then HIGHLIGHT ReportDate Else UNHIGHLIGHT ReportDate End-If End-After End-Field
Field Status After ASSIGN UPDATED=SYSTEMDATE End-After End-Field
